rtant%20to%20consider%20the%20mental%20and%20emotional%20aspects%20of%20that%20shift%2C%20there%20are%20also%20financial%20steps%20to%20take.%20When%20you're%20five%20years%20before%20or%20after%2C%20you're%20in%20what%20financial%20planning%20experts%20call%20the%20%26quot%3Bred%20zone%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20period%20when%20your%20savings%20and%20investing%20decisions%20can%20significantly%20impact%20your%20financial%20stability%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20your%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRetirement%20planning%20necessitates%20a%20long-term%20perspective%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Ashley%20Folkes%2C%20vice%20president%20and%20wealth%20manager%20at%20financial%20planning%20firm%20Farther.%20%26quot%3BAddressing%20anxieties%20related%20to%20healthcare%20costs%2C%20inflation%2C%20and%20unexpected%20expenses%20through%20thorough%20planning%20is%20essential.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20six%20moves%20financial%20planners%20say%20to%20make%20when%20you're%20five%20years%20out%20from%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2222e21002-95d8-4b46-b8f2-4345f63cb09d%5C%22%3E1.%20Figure%20out%20what%20you%20spend%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20first%20steps%20to%20transitioning%20to%20retirement%20is%20to%20determine%20how%20much%20you're%20currently%20spending%20so%20you%20can%20figure%20out%20how%20much%20money%20you'll%20need%20once%20you%20don't%20have%20a%20steady%20paycheck.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDon't%20go%20through%20the%20headache%20of%20creating%20an%20itemized%20budget%2C%20says%20Evan%20Beach%2C%20president%20and%20wealth%20advisor%20at%20Exit%2059%20Advisory.%20Instead%2C%20he%20recommends%20simply%20looking%20at%20two%20years%20of%20debits%20from%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fbest-banks%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebank%20account%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20dividing%20by%2024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20should%20capture%20those%20one-off%20items%2C%20but%20more%20importantly%2C%20gives%20you%20the%20information%20necessary%20to%20see%20if%20you're%20on%20track%2C%26quot%3B%20Beach%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ed34e676-d4a8-47c0-96a1-39832fb55050%5C%22%3E2.%20Do%20a%20trial%20run%20with%20your%20projected%20budget%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20strategic%20way%20to%20address%20the%20concern%20of%20outliving%20your%20savings%20or%20becoming%20a%20financial%20burden%20on%20your%20family%20is%20to%20simulate%20retirement%20living%20by%20adhering%20to%20a%20projected%20budget%2C%20Folkes%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20trial%20run%20reveals%20potential%20discrepancies%20between%20planned%20and%20actual%20expenses%2C%20prompting%20necessary%20adjustments%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20adds.%20If%20past%20financial%20constraints%2C%20such%20as%20paying%20a%20child's%20college%20tuition%2C%20have%20limited%20your%20savings%2C%20it's%20good%20to%20know%20that%20before%20you%20retire%2C%20and%20can%20still%20implement%20savings%20catch-up%20methods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227b8ef4b7-10bb-4be0-9e0f-ba5b4a26c271%5C%22%3E3.%20Maximize%20your%20savings%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20it%20may%20be%20a%20good%20idea%20to%20save%20aggressively%20during%20this%20time%2C%20even%20if%20you're%20already%20on%20track.%20Your%20last%20five%20years%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20your%20highest%20earnings%20years%2C%20and%20you%20may%20also%20have%20lower%20family%20expenses%20if%20you%20have%20children%20who%20have%20moved%20out%20of%20the%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHigh%20income%20and%20comparatively%20low%20expenses%20is%20the%20perfect%20recipe%20for%20those%20looking%20to%20supercharge%20their%20savings%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Jessica%20McNamee%2C%20founder%20and%20wealth%20management%20advisor%20at%20Sirius%20Wealth%20Strategies.%20%26quot%3BIn%20the%20last%20five%20years%20of%20work%2C%20people%20should%20try%20to%20maximize%20their%20retirement%20plan%20contributions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20don't%20get%20discouraged%20if%20that%20is%20not%20possible.%20McNamee%20says%20if%20clients%20can't%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2F401k-contribution-limits%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtribute%20the%20maximum%20amount%3C%2Fa%3E%20allowed%20by%20the%20IRS%2C%20she%20encourages%20them%20to%20contribute%20what%20they%20can%3A%20%26quot%3BSomething%20is%20better%20than%20nothing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20also%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20you%20have%20enough%20cash%20reserves.%20Consider%20how%20much%20of%20your%20expenses%20will%20be%20covered%20by%20guaranteed%20income%2C%20such%20as%20Social%20Security%20or%20a%20pension%2C%20as%20well%20as%20withdrawals%20from%20your%20retirement%20accounts%2C%20to%20determine%20what%20amount%20of%20cash%20you%20should%20have%20handy.%20(While%20you're%20at%20it%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ssa.gov%2Fprepare%2Freview-record-earnings%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereview%20your%20Social%20Security%20earnings%20records%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20make%20sure%20they're%20accurate.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dab32786-7083-4389-be1a-0e44f2699318%5C%22%3E4.%20Review%20your%20investment%20portfolio%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20you%20should%20be%20reviewing%20your%20asset%20allocation%20%E2%80%94%20how%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Finvestment-portfolio%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvestment%20portfolio%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20divided%20between%20assets%20such%20as%20stocks%20and%20bonds%20%E2%80%94%20regularly%2C%20it's%20essential%20to%20do%20a%20check-in%20when%20you're%20approaching%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBeing%20too%20risky%20just%20before%20and%20just%20after%20retirement%20can%20have%20huge%20consequences%20to%20you%20for%20literally%20the%20rest%20of%20your%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Monica%20Dwyer%2C%20senior%20vice%20president%20and%20wealth%20advisor%20at%20Harvest%20Financial%20Advisors.%20%26quot%3BHuge%20losses%20during%20the%20five%20years%20prior%20and%20a%20few%20years%20after%20your%20retirement%20can%20alter%20your%20trajectory%2C%20so%20be%20aware%20of%20those%20risks%20and%20adjust%20accordingly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20portfolio's%20asset%20allocation%20will%20be%20different%20for%20each%20investor%3A%20Someone%20who%20is%20less%20tolerant%20to%20risk%20and%20doesn't%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20cash%20saved%20up%20should%20take%20a%20different%20approach%20from%20someone%20who%20is%20risk%20intolerant%20but%20has%20wiggle%20room%20in%20the%20budget%2C%20or%20someone%20who%20can%20still%20invest%20aggressively%20amid%20market%20ups%20and%20downs.%20It%20may%20be%20worth%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fhow-to-find-financial-advisor%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinding%20a%20financial%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20can%20help%20you%20make%20appropriate%20adjustments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20also%20a%20good%20time%20to%20make%20sure%20your%20portfolio%20is%20tax%20diversified%20%E2%80%94%20as%20in%2C%20your%20money%20is%20(ideally)%20split%20between%20accounts%20with%20pre-tax%2C%20after-tax%2C%20and%20tax-free%20treatments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20gives%20you%20more%20options%2C%26quot%3B%20Dwyer%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225ed01f8f-b8f6-45de-9abf-9f41a78c27ee%5C%22%3E5.%20Take%20care%20of%20any%20needed%20home%20repairs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20seem%20easier%20to%20wait%20until%20you%20have%20more%20time%20in%20retirement%20to%20take%20care%20of%20home%20repairs%2C%20but%20Beach%20recommends%20trying%20to%20get%20them%20done%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOn%20the%20financial%20front%2C%20you%20typically%20have%20the%20most%20wiggle%20room%20between%20income%20and%20expenses%20between%20the%20time%20your%20kids%20leave%20the%20house%20and%20when%20you%20retire%2C%26quot%3B%20Beach%20says.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20the%20time%20to%