%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Meta%20CEO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-mark-zuckerberg-cant-be-fired-as-meta-facebook-ceo-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMark%20Zuckerberg%3C%2Fa%3E%20controls%20a%20majority%20of%20the%20company's%20voting%20shares%20through%20a%20dual-class%20stock%20structure%2C%20effectively%20giving%20him%20the%20power%20to%20decide%20the%20outcome%20of%20any%20shareholder%20vote.%20Even%20if%20outside%20investors%20broadly%20support%20the%20proposal%2C%20it%20is%20almost%20certain%20to%20fail%20without%20Zuckerberg's%20backing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20declined%20to%20comment.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta's%20board%20has%20urged%20shareholders%20to%20vote%20against%20the%20proposal%2C%20saying%20the%20company%20already%20has%20comprehensive%20content%20moderation%20systems%20and%20transparency%20reports%20and%20that%20an%20additional%20report%20would%20not%20provide%20meaningful%20new%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EADL%20and%20JLens%20argue%20that%20forcing%20the%20issue%20into%20public%20view%20and%20onto%20the%20ballot%20is%20an%20important%20step%20toward%20holding%20Meta%20accountable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20a%20one-time%20effort%2C%20but%20part%20of%20a%20broader%20push%20to%20ensure%20Meta%20takes%20meaningful%20responsibility%20for%20the%20harmful%20content%20that%20appears%20on%20its%20platforms%2C%26quot%3B%20Ari%20Hoffnung%2C%20managing%20director%20of%20JLens%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BTransparency%20is%20the%20necessary%20first%20step.%20Investors%20and%20the%20public%20need%20to%20understand%20what%20Meta%20is%20currently%20doing%20to%20combat%20hate%20on%20its%20platforms.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20ADL%20and%20JLens%20say%20Meta's%20current%20disclosures%20fall%20short%20and%20that%20independent%2C%20community-specific%20metrics%20are%20essential%20to%20understanding%20the%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20concerns%20about%20user%20safety%2C%20JLens%20also%20framed%20hate%20speech%20as%20a%20financial%20risk%20for%20Meta's%20shareholders.%20Hoffnung%20said%20harmful%20content%20on%20Meta%20could%20expose%20the%20company%20to%20legal%2C%20regulatory%2C%20and%20reputational%20risks%20and%20threaten%20relationships%20with%20advertisers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMeta%20is%20the%20platform%20where%20we've%20consistently%20identified%20as%20having%20one%20of%20the%20highest%20volumes%20of%20antisemitic%20and%20other%20hateful%20content%2C%20making%20it%20a%20priority%20for%20investor%20engagement%2C%26quot%3B%20Jonathan%20Greenblatt%2C%20CEO%20of%20ADL%2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BMeta%20also%20is%20a%20public%20company%2C%20and%20so%20as%20shareholders%2C%20we%20have%20a%20formal%20mechanism%20to%20push%20for%20transparency%20and%20accountability%20through%20resolutions%20like%20Proposal%208%2C%20which%20we%20believe%20is%20the%20most%20constructive%20way%20to%20drive%20lasting%20change%20from%20within%20the%20company.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ADL%2C%20founded%20in%201913%2C%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20prominent%20civil%20rights%20organizations%20in%20the%20US%20focused%20on%20combating%20antisemitism%20and%20hate.%20In%202022%2C%20it%20acquired%20JLens%2C%20a%20Jewish%20values-based%20investor%20network%2C%20giving%20it%20a%20formal%20foothold%20in%20shareholder%20advocacy.%20JLens%20manages%20investments%20in%20major%20public%20companies%2C%20including%20Meta%2C%20through%20funds%20aligned%20with%20Jewish%20values%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D71b0eb72a6c75d9724da950c559b36d3d8ddd7da59ef110e4387759cb0379569%26postID%3D680c1c6518fa533063269f7d%26postSlug%3Dmeta-push-transparency-hate-speech-2025-4%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.morningstar.com%252Fetfs%252Farcx%252Ftov%252Fportfolio%253Futm_source%253Dchatgpt.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20stakes%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20most%20large%20public%20companies%2C%20including%20Apple%2C%20Microsoft%2C%20Nvidia%2C%20and%20Meta.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20ADL%20does%20not%20directly%20own%20Meta%20stock%2C%20its%20acquisition%20of%20JLens%20enables%20it%20to%20influence%20corporate%20governance%20through%20shareholder%20proposals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20previously%20attempted%20to%20engage%20the%20company%20directly%20without%20success%2C%26quot%3B%20Hoffnung%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20year%2C%20we%20felt%20it%20was%20time%20to%20escalate%20our%20concerns%20through%20a%20shareholder%20proposal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShareholder%20proposals%20are%20a%20common%20tool%20during%20%26quot%3Bproxy%20season%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20period%20in%20spring%20when%20public%20companies%20hold%20annual%20meetings%20and%20shareholders%20vote%20on%20issues%20ranging%20from%20executive%20compensation%20to%20corporate%20social%20responsibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pressure%20on%20Meta%20comes%20as%20the%20company's%20own%20Oversight%20Board%2C%20an%20independent%20group%20funded%20by%20Meta%2C%20recently%20raised%20alarms%20about%20the%20company's%20approach%20to%20hate%20speech%20enforcement.%20In%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oversightboard.com%2Fnews%2Fwide-ranging-decisions-protect-speech-and-address-harms%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20week%2C%20the%20board%20criticized%20Meta's%20recent%20rollback%20of%20its%20moderation%20policies%20and%20warned%20that%20the%20changes%20could%20undermine%20user%20safety%20and%20brand%20trust.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGreenblatt%20said%20the%20ADL%20believes%20strongly%20in%20free%20expression%20but%20rejects%20the%20idea%20that%20it%20should%20come%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20user%20safety.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20strongly%20believe%20in%20the%20importance%20of%20free%20expression%2C%20but%20it%20cannot%20come%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20safety%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAntisemitic%20content%20and%20hate%20speech%20can%20lead%20to%20real-world%20harm%2C%20threats%2C%20and%20violence%20%E2%80%94%20as%20we've%20often%20seen%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20then%20crosses%20the%20line%20from%20protected%20expression%20into%20dangerous%20conduct.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGreenblatt%20pointed%20to%20Reddit's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fr%2FRedditSafety%2Fcomments%2Fpwo54j%2Fq2_safety_security_report%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etransparency%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20tracked%20incidents%20of%20Holocaust%20denial%20and%20other%20hate%20targeting%20specific%20groups%2C%20as%20a%20model%20for%20the%20kind%20of%20reporting%20they%20hope%20Meta%20will%20adopt%20if%20Proposal%208%20is%20successful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProposal%208%20is%20one%20of%20several%20measures%20investors%20will%20consider%20at%20Meta's%20annual%20meeting.%20Other%20shareholder%20proposals%20to%20be%20voted%20on%20include%20calls%20for%20greater%20transparency%20around%20child%20safety%20risks%2C%20oversight%20of%20Meta's%20use%20of%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20and%20enhanced%20reporting%20on%20how%20the%20company's%20data%20collection%20practices%20affect%20user%20privacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJLens%20has%20been%20active%20beyond%20Meta%20this%20year.%20It%20has%20filed%20shareholder%20letters%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sec.gov%2FArchives%2Fedgar%2Fdata%2F50863%2F000092189525001059%2Fpx14a6g14098intc_04112025.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIntel%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sec.gov%2FArchives%2Fedgar%2Fdata%2F2016320%2F000092189525000992%2Fpx14a6g14098008_04042025.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGeneral%20Dynamics%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sec.gov%2FArchives%2Fedgar%2Fdata%2F2016320%2F000092189525000993%2Fpx14a6g14098009_04042025.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELockheed%20Martin%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20urging%20rejection%20of%20proposals%20it%20viewed%20as%20anti-Israel.%20During%20the%202024%20proxy%20season%2C%20JLens%20and%20t