-a9a5-a00116a5d499%5C%22%3EBe%20a%20language%20mirror%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDeveloping%20allies%20is%20the%20universal%20secret%20to%20influence%2C%20but%20it's%20even%20more%20important%20when%20the%20stakes%20are%20high.%20Given%20the%20anxiety%2C%20strong%20opinions%2C%20and%20office%20politics%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20org%20chart%2C%20executives%20are%20all%20the%20more%20on%20the%20lookout%20for%20who's%20on%20their%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20learned%20early%20in%20my%20career%20to%20listen%20carefully%20and%20reflect%20the%20specific%20words%20that%20executives%20use%20back%20to%20them%20%E2%80%94%20a%20method%20sometimes%20called%20%26quot%3Blinguistic%20mirroring.%26quot%3B%20This%20technique%20works%20because%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fworklife%2Farticle%2F20201214-how-linguistic-mirroring-can-make-you-more-convincing%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elanguage%20people%20use%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20map%20to%20the%20arguments%20they're%20most%20likely%20to%20buy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20execute%20linguistic%20mirroring%20well%2C%20I%20paid%20close%20attention%20to%20the%20speech%20patterns%20and%20word%20choices%20executives%20used%20in%20a%20specific%20context%20and%20then%20subtly%20reflected%20those%20verbal%20cues%20in%20my%20speech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20when%20I%20disagreed%20with%20an%20executive%2C%20I%20found%20it%20more%20persuasive%20to%20express%20myself%20using%20language%20that%20I'd%20unabashedly%20stolen%20from%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20I%20was%20once%20asked%20to%20lead%20a%20major%20reorganization%20project%20and%20disagreed%20with%20an%20executive's%20initial%20design.%20I%20noticed%20their%20rationale%20was%20framed%20around%20improving%20efficiency%2C%20and%20even%20though%20I%20believed%20efficiency%20wasn't%20a%20top%20concern%2C%20I%20used%20efficiency-centered%20language%20to%20pitch%20my%20alternative%20approach%2C%20successfully%20persuading%20them%20to%20adopt%20my%20design.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e4cc51c8-601a-41cb-ad9e-938973d052a9%5C%22%3ENever%20present%20a%20blank%20slate%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESenior%20executives%20are%20usually%20forced%20to%20cover%20a%20lot%20of%20territory%20and%20switch%20contexts%20with%20every%20meeting.%20When%20presenting%20to%20them%2C%20the%20challenge%20is%20often%20to%20focus%20their%20attention%20on%20your%20topic%20quickly%20without%20wasting%20time%20getting%20them%20up%20to%20speed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20trick%20for%20doing%20this%20well%20was%20to%20avoid%20presenting%20a%20blank%20slate.%20I%20learned%20never%20to%20present%20an%20open%20question%20without%20adding%20an%20answer%20or%20to%20discuss%20a%20plan%20without%20sharing%20the%20progress%20I'd%20already%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20sound%20presumptuous%20to%20skip%20ahead%2C%20but%20I%20found%20that%20sharing%20my%20progress%20as%20a%20starting%20point%2C%20rather%20than%20simply%20presenting%20the%20project%20context%2C%20helped%20execs%20understand%20quickly%20and%20focus%20their%20feedback%20on%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20I%20was%20once%20tasked%20with%20leading%20a%20complex%20project%20that%20would%20require%20coordinating%20with%20leaders%20and%20teams%20across%20the%20product%20org%20and%20then%20getting%20executives%20to%20sign%20off.%20Instead%20of%20simply%20presenting%20a%20project%20plan%2C%20I%20quickly%20completed%20a%20straightforward%20part%20and%20presented%20my%20progress%20as%20an%20introduction%20to%20the%20project.%20It%20allowed%20them%20to%20quickly%20understand%20what%20the%20project%20was%20about%20and%20what%20I%20needed%20from%20them%20%E2%80%94%20an%20effective%20shortcut%20to%20getting%20sign-off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b2bea896-0f31-4f9d-b3ac-a179f878b07f%5C%22%3EPresent%20ideas%20in%20pairs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20senior%20executives%20become%20used%20to%20driving%20decisions%20with%20their%20intuition%2C%20preference%2C%20and%20taste.%3C%2Fp%3E%3