0Images%3B%20Social%20Security%20Administration%3B%20Chelsea%20Jia%20Feng%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Social%20Security%20Administration%20faces%20a%20delicate%20moment.%20Its%20future%20teeters%20between%20a%20career%20bureaucrat%20and%20a%20former%20Citigroup%20and%20JPMorgan%20Chase%20executive%20who%20may%20bring%20order%20%E2%80%94%20or%20further%20tumult.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%20maintains%20the%20country's%20largest%20safety%20net.%20It%20employs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ssa.gov%2Forg%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enearly%2060%2C000%20federal%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20provides%20benefits%20to%20over%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ssa.gov%2Fpolicy%2Fdocs%2Fquickfacts%2Fstat_snapshot%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E73%20million%20Americans%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20has%20long%20been%20seen%20as%20untouchable%20in%20Washington%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bthe%20third%20rail%20of%20American%20politics%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20and%20commissioners%20rarely%20leave%2C%20even%20as%20presidential%20administrations%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20changed%20in%20February%2C%20when%20Michelle%20King%2C%20a%2030-year%20veteran%20of%20the%20agency%2C%20abruptly%20left%20her%20role%20as%20acting%20commissioner.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIn%20her%20place%2C%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20installed%20Leland%20Dudek%2C%20an%20employee%20who%20wasn't%20in%20the%20agency's%20executive%20ranks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20transition%2C%20which%20came%20as%20DOGE%20staffers%20accessed%20internal%20agency%20data%2C%20one%20worker's%20affidavit%20said%2C%20was%20a%20sharp%20departure%20from%20typical%20agency%20protocol.%20It%20%26quot%3Bwas%20a%20shock%20to%20every%20single%20person%20that%20works%20at%20SSA%2C%26quot%3B%20Laura%20Haltzel%2C%20a%20former%20Social%20Security%20associate%20commissioner%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20It%20was%20also%20a%20harbinger%20of%20the%20chaos%20to%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20the%20White%20House%20DOGE%20office%20has%20slashed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-security-offices-doge-cutting-most-customer-service-workers-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estaff%20numbers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20policy%20flip-flops%20have%20put%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-security-retiree-benefits-calls-office-visits-retirees-worry-checks-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebeneficiaries%20on%20edge%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Dudek%20weighed%20closing%20the%20agency%20based%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabcnews.go.com%2FPolitics%2Facting-social-security-chief-now-shut-agency-after%2Fstory%3Fid%3D120046608%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eon%20his%20understanding%20of%20a%20judge's%20ruling%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20AARP%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faarp-warns-social-security-customer-service-retirees-benefits-staff-cuts-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20things%20may%20get%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Frank%20Bisignano%2C%20a%20finance%20titan%20and%20formidable%20turnaround%20manager%2C%20is%20waiting%20in%20the%20wings%20as%20Trump's%20nominee%20to%20replace%20Dudek.%20The%20transition%20ahead%20could%20set%20the%20course%20for%20how%20%E2%80%94%20and%20how%20well%20%E2%80%94%20millions%20of%20Americans%20receive%20their%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2254213032-2140-4759-b829-fef962489cba%5C%22%3EThe%20turnaround%20agent%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.finance.senate.gov%2Fimo%2Fmedia%2Fdoc%2F032525_bisignano_testimony.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBisignano%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2065%2C%20is%20the%20chair%20and%20CEO%20of%20Fiserv%2C%20a%20global%20fintech%20giant.%20He%20was%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Finteractive%2F2018%2F05%2F25%2Fbusiness%2Fceo-pay-2017.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esecond-highest-paid%20CEO%20in%20the%20US%20in%202017%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20when%20he%20earned%20more%20than%20%24100%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20in%20the%20industry%20told%20BI%20they%20see%20him%20as%20a%20turnaround%20artist%2C%20which%20could%20serve%20him%20well%20should%20he%20take%20over%20the%20agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBisignano's%20confirmation%20is%20awaiting%20a%20full%20Senate%20vote%2C%20which%20is%20expected%20after%20the%20chamber%20votes%20on%20nominees%20for%20multiple%20diplomatic%20positions.%20He%20has%20already%20appeared%20before%20the%20Senate%20Finance%20Committee%2C%20where%20he%20addressed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-security-privatization-frank-bisignano-hearing-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econcerns%20about%20privatization%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BI've%20never%20thought%20about%20privatizing.%20It's%20not%20a%20word%20that%20anybody's%20ever%20talked%20to%20me%20about%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20lawmakers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20official%20on%20the%20transition%20team%20shepherding%20Trump's%20nominees%20through%20the%20confirmation%20process%20declined%20to%20comment%20for%20this%20story%20or%20make%20Bisignano%20available%20for%20an%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20who%20spoke%20with%20BI%20expressed%20surprise%20that%20he%20would%20join%20the%20Trump%20administration.%20An%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20150208061904%2Fhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.firstdata.com%2Fen_us%2Fabout-first-data%2Fleadership-team%2Ffrank-bisignano-bio.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Earchived%20biography%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20First%20Data%2C%20where%20he%20served%20as%20chair%20and%20CEO%2C%20said%20he's%20%26quot%3Ba%20strong%20supporter%20of%20diversity%26quot%3B%20and%20helped%20create%20affinity%20groups%20for%20women%20and%20LGBTQ%2B%20employees%20at%20the%20company.%20He's%20donated%20to%20candidates%20on%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20aisle%2C%20including%20Sen.%20Chuck%20Schumer%2C%20a%20Democrat%20from%20New%20York%2C%20and%20Florida's%20Republican%20governor%2C%20Ron%20DeSantis%2C%20records%20show.%20In%20May%202019%2C%20Bisignano%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fec.gov%2Fdata%2Freceipts%2Findividual-contributions%2F%3Fcontributor_name%3DFrank%2BBisignano%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egave%3C%2Fa%3E%20%24125%2C000%20to%20the%20Trump%20Victory%20PAC%20and%20another%20%2483%2C900%20to%20the%20Republican%20National%20Committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22frank%20bisignano%20stands%20during%20confirmation%20hearing%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F680bc564a466d2b74ab43398%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFrank%20Bisignano%20during%20his%20confirmation%20hearing.%3Cp%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBorn%20in%20Brooklyn%2C%20with%20a%20father%20who%20was%20an%20orphan%20and%20a%20grandfather%20who%20emigrated%20from%20Italy%2C%20Bisignano%20first%20landed%20on%20Wall%20Street%20in%20the%201970s.%20He%20started%20out%20at%20smaller%20firms%20before%20joining%20the%20legendary%20bankers%20Sandy%20Weill%20and%20Jamie%20Dimon%20as%20they%20built%20what%20would%20become%20Citigroup.%20There%2C%20he%20managed%20the%20company's%20global%20transaction%20services%20business%2C%20helping%20steer%20trillions%20of%20dollars%20in%20payments%20worldwide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20knew%20enough%20about%20the%20guts%20of%20the%20operations%20he%20was%20involved%20in%20to%20be%20able%20to%20be%20a%20very%20good%20manager%2C%26quot%3B%20Weill%2C%20a%20former%20chair%20and%20CEO%20of%20Citigroup%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELater%2C%20he%20joined%20JPMorgan%20Chase%2C%20where%20he%20reversed%20multibillion-dollar%20losses%20in%20the%20firm's%20mortgage%20banking%20unit%20and%20rose%20to%20become%20its%20co-chief%20operating%20officer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFrank%20did%20a%20very%20good%20job%20in%20operations%20for%20JPMorgan%2C%20but%20I%20think%20that%20he%20was%20looking%20for%20something%20where%20he%20would%20be%20able%20to%20test%20his%20leadership%20skills%20beyond%20operations%2C%26quot%3B%20Weill%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202013%2C%20he%20took%20over%20First%20Data.%20Its%20owner%20at%20the%20time%2C%20the%20private%20equity%20giant%20KKR%2C%20was%20seeking%20a%20CEO%20with%20knowledge%20of%20payments%20and%20back-office%20systems.%20He%20steered%20the%20company%20through%20its%20%242.6%20billion%20initial%20public%20offering%20and%20its%20%2422%20billion%20sale%20to%20Fiserv%20in%202019%3B%20he%20became%20Fiserv's%20CEO%20the%20following%20year.%20Under%20his%20tenure%2C%20the%20company's%20stock%20price%20has%20roughly%20doubled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Farticles%2F2025%2F04%2Ftrump-effect-a-running-list-of-new-u-s-investment-in-president-trumps-second-term%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epost%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20official%20White%20House%20website%20in%20late%20April%20touted%20the%20%26quot%3BTrump%20effect%2C%26quot%3B%20crediting%20the%20president%20for%20spurring%20a%20series%20of%20private%20sector%20investments%20in%20American%20industry.%20Among%20those%20the%20administration%20pointed%20to%3A%20Fiserv's%20%24175%20million%20commitment%20to%20develop%20a%20427%2C000-square-foot%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finvestors.fiserv.com%2Fnewsroom%2Fdetail%2F2836%2Ffiserv-and-kansas-team-up-to-launch-strategic-fintech-hub%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efintech%20campus%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Kansas%2C%20which%20is%20expected%20to%20drive%20the%20creation%20of%202%2C000%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221885e01c-e7ad-4017-8233-1be063a78217%5C%22%3ELeland%20Dudek's%20turbulent%20tenure%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECurrently%20leading%20the%20agency%20%E2%80%94%20and%20seen%20by%20some%20SSA%20insiders%20as%20responsible%20for%20much%20of%20the%20recent%20turmoil%20%E2%80%94%20is%20Dudek%2C%20the%20acting%20commissioner%20Trump%20installed%20in%20February.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20former%20senior%20Social%20Security%20official%20who%20was%20familiar%20with%20the%20senior-level%20employees%20usually%20tapped%20for%20the%20role%20remembered%20thinking%3A%20%26quot%3BWho%20is%20this%20guy%3F%26quot%3B%20A%20director-level%20employee%20who's%20on%20administrative%20leave%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Etold%20BI%20that%20Dudek%2C%2048%2C%20was%20%26quot%3Ba%20nobody%20until%20a%20month%20ago.%26quot%3B%20(Most%20of%20the%20SSA%20sources%20who%20spoke%20with%20BI%20left%20within%20the%20past%20few%20months.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20recently%2C%20Dudek%20had%20been%20serving%20as%20a%20senior%20advisor%20in%20the%20agency's%20Office%20of%20Program%20Integrity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDudek%2C%20who%20holds%20degrees%20from%20the%20Catholic%20University%20of%20America%20and%20the%20National%20Defense%20University%2C%20has%20long%20been%20enmeshed%20in%20anti-fraud%20and%20information%20technology%20work.%20According%20to%20an%20agency%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ssa.gov%2Fagency%2Fcommissioner%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebiography%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20previously%20served%20as%20the%20chief%20information%20security%20officer%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.federalregister.gov%2Fagencies%2Frecovery-accountability-and-transparency-board%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERecovery%20Accountability%20and%20Transparency%20Board%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20has%20been%20with%20the%20SSA%20since%202009%2C%20though%20he%20does%20not%20appear%20on%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20250202090831%2Fhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.ssa.gov%2Forg%2FagencyOrg.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eorganizational%20chart%3C%2Fa%3E%20archived%20immediately%20before%20King's%20departure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20former%20manager%20at%20SSA%20who%20met%20Dudek%20when%20he%20arrived%20at%20the%20agency%20said%20that%20he%20%26quot%3Bseemed%20like%20a%20pretty%20earnest%2C%20straightforward%20kind%20of%20computer%20science%20IT%20type%20who%20had%20experience%20outside%20the%20agency.%26quot%3B%20Dudek%2C%20this%20person%20said%2C%20was%20part%20of%20a%20larger%20group%20who%20felt%20the%20agency%20was%20slow%20to%20adopt%20technological%20advances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20generally%20seemed%20to%20be%20interested%20in%20things%20running%20more%20effectively%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20former%20SSA%20employee%20said.%20They%20described%20him%20as%20being%20frustrated%20over%20%26quot%3Btrying%20to%20make%20change%20and%20do%20things%20in%20a%20bureaucratic%20environment%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20other%20employees%20at%20his%20level%20felt%20similarly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20former%20SSA%20executive%20said%20they%20believed%20he%20had%20good%20intentions%20and%20genuinely%20cared%20about%20curbing%20fraud%20and%20improper%20payments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20path%20at%20the%20agency%20was%20not%20straightforward.%20Elon%20Musk%20said%20on%20X%20that%20Dudek%20was%20%26quot%3Bfired%26quot%3B%20for%20%26quot%3Bhelping%20%40DOGE%20find%20taxpayer%20savings%26quot%3B%20before%20he%20ascended%20to%20SSA's%20highest%20perch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%2C%20he%20brought%20his%20own%20style.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20he%20felt%20like%20he%20deserved%20a%20voice%20at%20the%20table%2C%20and%20then%20he%20suddenly%20got%20one%20and%20didn't%20quite%20know%20what%20to%20do%20with%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20former%20executive%20said.%20The%20executive%20added%20that%20Dudek%20appeared%20to%20have%20competing%20priorities%20between%20staff%20cuts%20and%20making%20sure%20the%20agency%20ran%20smoothly.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20been%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20yo-yo%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20unusual%2C%20very%20unusual%20leadership%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Kathleen%20Romig%2C%20who%20worked%20at%20the%20agency%20for%20nine%20years%20on%20and%20off%20and%20now%20serves%20as%20the%20director%20of%20Social%20Security%20and%20disability%20policy%20at%20the%20Center%20on%20Budget%20and%20Policy%20Priorities.%20Many%20of%20his%20decisions%20seemed%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bhasty%20and%20ill-considered%2C%26quot%3B%20Romig%20said.%20Some%2C%20like%20shuttering%20the%20agency%20or%20changing%20in-person%20identification%20guidelines%2C%20were%20ultimately%20reversed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20never%20seen%20leadership%20like%20this%20before%20at%20SSA%2C%20by%20a%20long%20shot%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20press%20call%20in%20March%2C%20Dudek%20said%20some%20contracts%20in%20Maine%20that%20let%20parents%20register%20their%20newborn%20children%20for%20an%20SSA%20number%20were%20%26quot%3Bcanceled%20because%20I%20screwed%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20made%20the%20wrong%20move%20there.%20I%20should%20always%20ask%20my%20staff%20for%20guidance%20first%20before%20I%20cancel%20something%2C%26quot%3B%20Dudek%20said.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20new%20at%20this%20job.%20It%20looked%20fishy.%26quot%3B%20The%20contracts%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wbur.org%2Fnews%2F2025%2F03%2F07%2Fmaine-enumeration-at-birth-social-security-babies-musk%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eultimately%20reinstated%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDudek%20and%20the%20Social%20Security%20Administration%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20multiple%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225013%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Social%20Security%20Administration%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b4d1137bb3f854015d2656%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223406%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Trump%20Administration%20is%20targeting%20the%20Social%20Security%20Administration%20for%20suspected%20fraud.%3Cp%3EVALERIE%20MACON%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20appointment%20pushed%20at%20least%20one%20SSA%20worker%20to%20leave.%20When%20they%20saw%20reports%20that%20he'd%20shared%20information%20with%20DOGE%20and%20was%20still%20elevated%2C%20%26quot%3Bit%20just%20all%20became%20a%20farce%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20former%20worker%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20person%20who%20has%20spoken%20with%20Dudek%20said%20they%20believed%20some%20of%20his%20bluster%20might%20be%20a%20smoke%20screen.%20They%20said%20Dudek%2C%20like%20previous%20commissioners%2C%20said%20he%20feared%20that%20the%20system%20was%20on%20the%20brink%20of%20collapse%20and%20worried%20about%20people%20not%20receiving%20their%20benefits%20%E2%80%94%20a%20similar%20sentiment%20to%20what%20Dudek%20expressed%20in%20a%20recording%20obtained%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.propublica.org%2Farticle%2Frecording-reveals-leland-dudek-thoughts-trump-doge-social-security%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EProPublica%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20feel%20that%20he%20thinks%20he's%20doing%20damage%20control%20and%20running%20interference%20between%20DOGE%20and%20everyone%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20felt%20like%20a%20bunch%20of%206-year-olds%20with%20too%20much%20sugar%20had%20been%20put%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20agency%20and%20were%20just%20kind%20of%20running%20all%20over%20the%20place%2C%20randomly%20disconnecting%20and%20reconnecting%20things%20in%20different%20ways%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20former%20SSA%20manager%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f789f5d8-a3cf-4c1e-99da-37c7776ad91b%5C%22%3EBisignano's%20high-stakes%20challenge%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20what%20awaits%20Bisignano%2C%20who%20has%20developed%20a%20reputation%20as%20a%20hard-charging%2C%20demanding%20executive%20who%20tends%20to%20see%20Saturdays%20as%20just%20another%20workday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20was%20always%20making%20sure%20that%20everybody%20had%20their%20nose%20to%20the%20grindstone%2C%26quot%3B%20Weill%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20he's%20moved%20from%20company%20to%20company%2C%20Bisignano%20has%20surrounded%20himself%20with%20a%20cadre%20of%20deputies%2C%20some%20of%20whom%20have%20been%20with%20him%20since%20his%20JPMorgan%20Chase%20days.%20Another%20person%20who%20knows%20Bisignano%20said%20some%20of%20these%20loyalists%20had%20shown%20they'd%20follow%20his%20lead%20without%20question%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20big%20the%20ask.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20going%20to%20pick%20up%20any%20call%20from%20Frank%20any%20time%20of%20day%20%E2%80%94%20morning%2C%20night%2C%20Saturday%2C%20Sunday%2C%207%20a.m.%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20person%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20decisions%20at%20Fiserv%20that%20played%20out%20on%20Bisignano's%20watch%20appear%20to%20have%20rankled%20some%20of%20his%20employees.%20A%20former%20Fiserv%20client%20project%20manager%20said%20that%20return-to-office%20policies%20rolled%20out%20late%20last%20year%20under%20Bisignano%20contributed%20to%20his%20decision%20to%20leave.%20The%20former%20manager%20described%20the%20culture%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20bit%20of%20a%20sweatshop.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%20Thanksgiving%2C%20Fiserv%20implemented%20new%20return-to-office%20guidance%2C%20calling%20some%20personnel%20managers%20back%20to%20their%20desks%20five%20days%20a%20week%20and%20instructing%20other%20workers%20to%20spend%20about%20nine%20hours%20a%20day%20at%20the%20office%2C%20an%20internal%20communication%20reviewed%20by%20BI%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20Fiserv%20employee%20credited%20Bisignano%20with%20getting%20results%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20do%20think%20he%20was%20part%20of%20the%20reason%20Fiserv%20is%20so%20profitable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20Fiserv%20pointed%20to%20a%20122%25%20rise%20in%20its%20stock%20under%20Bisignano's%20leadership%2C%20attributing%20his%20%26quot%3Bvision%26quot%3B%20to%20driving%20innovation%20across%20technology%20and%20payments.%20The%20company%20also%20cited%20his%20%26quot%3Bcommitment%20to%20investing%20in%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20including%20veterans%20and%20small-business%20owners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20Bisignano's%20no-nonsense%20approach%20will%20be%20as%20effective%20in%20running%20the%20government's%20biggest%20safety%20net%20as%20it%20was%20in%20vaulting%20him%20to%20the%20zenith%20of%20corporate%20America%20is%20an%20open%20question.%20So%20is%20what%20a%20dynamic%20might%20look%20like%20with%20his%20peers%20in%20the%20administration%2C%20like%20the%20former%20Wall%20Streeters%20Howard%20Lutnick%20and%20Scott%20Bessent%2C%20or%20Musk%2C%20who%20has%20acted%20as%20DOGE's%20public%20face.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20may%20soon%20find%20himself%20standing%20between%20policy%20whiplash%20from%20Washington%20and%20the%20checks%20that%20millions%20of%20older%20Americans%20depend%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBisignano%20%26quot%3Bloves%20his%20reputation%20for%20fixing%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20person%20who%20worked%20closely%20with%20him%2C%20%26quot%3Bnot%20for%20burning%20things%20down.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAllie%20Kelly%20contributed%20reporting.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-security-administration-leland-dudek-frank-bisignano-transition-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1745830802000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6807c38a3fe8d3928363b642%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-security-administration-leland-dudek-frank-bisignano-transition-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Acting%20commissioner%20Leland%20Dudek%20helms%20the%20nearly%2060%2C000-person%20federal%20agency.%20Frank%20Bisignano%2C%20a%20former%20JPMorgan%20Chase%20and%20Citigroup%20executive%2C%20waits%20in%20the%20wings.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jkaplan%40businessinsider.com%20(Juliana%20Kaplan%2CReed%20Alexander%2CDakin%20Campbell)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A122%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-security